{% set notes %}
{% spaceless %}
  <bolt-ol>
    <bolt-li>The Table Element is designed to work with both Twig and vanilla HTML (Twig is the recommended method).</bolt-li>
    <bolt-li>Refer to the <a href="{{ link['elements-table-headers-footers'] }}" class="e-bolt-text-link">Table Element with Headers and Footer</a> page for information on adding the headers and footer.</bolt-li>
    <bolt-li><strong>Twig:</strong> Use the <code>fixed_width_columns</code> prop to adjust the column widths.</bolt-li>
    <bolt-li><strong>HTML:</strong> Add a <code>e-bolt-table--fixed-width-columns--first</code>, <code>e-bolt-table--fixed-width-columns--second</code> or <code>e-bolt-table--fixed-width-columns--first-two</code> class to the <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> to adjust the column widths.</bolt-li>
